      `Riley is working on a difficult project and has been going through the motions for two hours. The body is present. The mind has partially checked out. The output is technically produced but not at the level Riley knows they are capable of.`,
      `Stop and identify the specific moment when the mind disengaged. Was it a difficult problem that felt unsolvable? Fatigue from a long week? Distraction? Then make a deliberate choice to re-engage with the specific hard part rather than staying in the comfortable zone of going through the motions.`,
      `Going through the motions produces output without genuine engagement. Goggins's principle applied to knowledge work means treating the moment of mental disengagement as the moment to re-engage deliberately, not as permission to coast.`
